value.value: Portion of tissue that is part of the heart tube and will become the bulbus arteriosus.
Multi-tissue structure that is part of the heart tube and will become the cardiac ventricle.

label.value: presumptive cardiac ventricle primitive heart tube

value.value: Portion of tissue that is part of the heart tube and will become the endocardium.
Portion of tissue that is part of the heart tube and will become the sinus venosus.
Podocyte that is part of the pronephros.
Multi-tissue structure that is the external layer of the swim bladder that is covered by the peritoneum, and made of elastic fibres and ichthyocol (short needles of collagen).

Multi-tissue structure that is the internal layer of the swim bladder and is comprised of thin endoderm and a smooth muscle layer called the muscularis mucosa with longitudinal and circular fibres with some collagen.
Endocardium that is part of the cardiac ventricle.
Surface structure that is the anteriormost region of the lower jaw.
Organism subdivision that is the side of the body possessing eyes.
Organism subdivision that is the side of the body lacking eyes.
Protuberance on a bone that participates in a joint with another bone.
Joint that articulates the premaxilla and maxilla. Premaxillary-maxillary joint is paired.
Pharyngeal arch cartilage located between uncinate process of epibranchial 1 and pharyngobranchial 2.

definition.value: An interarcual cartilage is present in percomorph fishes (Johnson and Patterson 1993).

value.value: Ctenoid scale with two or three alternating rows of cteni marginally and truncated cteni submarginally. (Roberts 1993).

Anatomical cluster that includes the terminal supraorbital neuromast(s) contained in the nasal bone and innervated by the buccal nerve, contact between the nasal bone and lacrimal, and contact between the supraorbital and infraorbital canals. (Johnson and Patterson 1993).
Joint that articulates the preopercle and opercle. Preopercle-opercle joint is paired.
